profile_positions.description:
Shell Internal Audit:
Responsible to lead and deliver key insights from risk-based auditing of operated / non-operated assets across business spectrum (Upstream, Integrated Gas, Unconventionals, New Business Development, Divestments.) and business risks: commercial aspects of divestments, asset management and development, exploration, assurance, governance, business financial planning incl commercial parameters, supply chain, modelling, forecasting and reporting of hydrocarbons and full GHG control framework.
Audit experience in assessing design and operating effectiveness of controls to mitigate risks around: 
•	Governance and business management processes;
•	Hydrocarbon resource and reserve estimation, classification, and reporting processes according to internal and external (SEC) controls;
•	Business Planning and performance management processes;
•	Processes enabling quality decision making;
•	Processes controlling interfaces and internal and external stakeholders, as such partners, authorities;
•	Processes around record management.
